### Section 4: Attribution Requirements (Mandatory)

4.1 **Retain Notices** — You must retain all copyright, patent, and attribution notices from the source form of Morget.

4.2 **NOTICE File** — If Morget includes a "NOTICE" text file as part of its distribution, You must include a readable copy of it in Your distribution. The NOTICE file is for informational purposes only and does not impose additional legally binding obligations beyond those stated in this license.

4.3 **Prominent Original Author Attribution (Critical)** — You MUST include a clear and visible attribution to the original authors in any project, product, or service that uses Morget Software or Morget Assets. You may fulfill this requirement in ANY ONE of the following ways:

(a) Include the attribution in the project's README file;
(b) Include the attribution in the NOTICE file distributed with Your project;
(c) Display the attribution in the user interface (e.g., About page, settings menu, footer, or splash screen);
(d) Include the attribution in the main documentation page or user guide.

The attribution must be in the following or equivalent form:

> "Based on Morget — Copyright (C) 2026 Moonlight Games (MG) / MGFeng / Feng"

or:

> "Contains components from Morget — Copyright (C) 2026 Moonlight Games (MG) / MGFeng / Feng"

This attribution MUST be easily accessible to end-users and developers interacting with Your project. Failure to comply with Section 4.3 constitutes a material breach of this license.

4.4 **Acceptable Forms** — You may reference the original authors using any of the following: "Moonlight Games", "MG", "MGFeng", "Feng", or "Moonlight Games (MG)".

4.5 **Your Own Work** — You may add Your own copyright notice to Your contributions, but You may not remove or obscure the original Morget copyright notice.

